INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jht3000','letter','1775-07-13','Lebanon','CT','US','Jonathan','Trumbull','','George','Washington','','individual','','Suffer me to join in congratulating you, on your appointment to be General and Commander-in-Chief of the troops raised, or to be raised, for the defence of American liberty.','ltr_jht3000.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume I., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jht3001','letter','1775-07-17','Lebanon','CT','US','Jonathan','Trumbull','','George','Washington','','individual','','On the 1st instant I met the Honorable Assembly of this Colony, to deliberate on the request and pressing reasons sent us from the Massachusetts for an immediate augmentation of troops from this Colony.','ltr_jht3001.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume I., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jht3002','letter','1775-07-31','Lebanon','CT','US','Jonathan','Trumbull','','George','Washington','','individual','','By the resolve in Congress of the 19th instant, it is recommended to the New England Colonies to complete the deficiencies in the -regiments belonging to them respectively.','ltr_jht3002.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume I., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jht3003','letter','1775-08-11','Lebanon','CT','US','Jonathan','Trumbull','','George','Washington','','individual','','I am informed a quantity of powder for the camp is to be at Hartford this evening, and more to follow soon. We have none lately arrived, which is daily expected.','ltr_jht3003.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume I., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jht3004','letter','1775-09-05','Lebanon','CT','US','Jonathan','Trumbull','','George','Washington','','individual','','Our coasts are kept in continual alarm. Three ships of war, with thirteen other vessels of divers sorts, were seen off Fisher\'s Island, and in the Sound, yesterday. ','ltr_jht3004.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume I., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jht3005','letter','1775-09-15','Lebanon','CT','US','Jonathan','Trumbull','','George','Washington','','individual','','New London and Stonington are still so menaced by the ministerial ships and troops, that the militia can not be thought sufficient for their security, and it is necessary to cast up some intrenchments.','ltr_jht3005.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume I., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jht3006','letter','1776-01-24','Lebanon','CT','US','Jonathan','Trumbull','','George','Washington','','individual','','I thought fit this morning to acquaint Colonel Burrell, appointed to command the regiment destined to Canada from hence, that a month\'s pay will be advanced to officers and men by you.','ltr_jht3006.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume I., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jht3007','letter','1776-02-05','Lebanon','CT','US','Jonathan','Trumbull','','George','Washington','','individual','','The battalion raising in this Colony, to march to the assistance of our friends at Canada, are enlisted to serve until the 1st of February next, with bounty, pay, wages, and allowances, agreeable to resolve of Congress','ltr_jht3007.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume I., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jht3008','letter','1776-02-12','Lebanon','CT','US','Jonathan','Trumbull','','George','Washington','','individual','','I am greatly concerned for the scarcity of powder and arms. We have not half a sufficiency for our selves, as the circumstances may be ; yet, anxious to furnish you, for the common good, with every supply in our power','ltr_jht3008.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume I., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jht3009','letter','1776-07-04','Lebanon','CT','US','Jonathan','Trumbull','','George','Washington','','individual','','The retreat of the Northern army, and its present situation, have spread a general alarm. By intelligence from Major-General Schuyler, received last-evening, I have reason to conclude that they are now at Crown Point and Ticonderoga, in a weak state','ltr_jht3009.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume I., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jht3010','letter','1776-01-15','Lebanon','CT','US','Jonathan','Trumbull','','George','Washington','','individual','','The condition and circumstances of the Colony of New York give me pain, lest the friends to American liberty in that Colony should be too much neglected and become disheartened','ltr_jht3010.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume I., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jht3011','letter','1776-08-05','Lebanon','CT','US','Jonathan','Trumbull','','George','Washington','','individual','','The troops from this State, destined to the northward, are marched to Bennington, and from thence to Skenesborough.','ltr_jht3011.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume I., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jht3012','letter','1777-02-21','Lebanon','CT','US','Jonathan','Trumbull','','George','Washington','','individual','','although it would have made me very happy to have been able to procure a release of all our officers in captivity, I freely acknowledge and acquiesce in the justice and impartiality of the measures you have taken respecting them.','ltr_jht3012.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume I., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jht3013','letter','1776-01-01','Lebanon','CT','US','Jonathan','Trumbull','','George','Washington','','individual','','By accounts received from the various parts of the Colony, the recruiting officers, for the Continental service, have good success in enlisting men.','ltr_jht3013.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume I., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jht3014','letter','1776-10-11','New Haven','CT','US','Jonathan','Trumbull','','George','Washington','','individual','','Our naval expedition against the ships of the enemy in the Sound is still in contemplation, and preparations are making for the same as fast as we can.','ltr_jht3014.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume I., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jht3200','letter','1779-05-29','Hartford','CT','US','Jonathan','Trumbull','','George','Washington','','individual','','I suppose your Excellency is not wholly unacquainted with the character of Mr. David Bushnell, the bearer. He has had a liberal education, and discovers a genius capable of great improvement','ltr_jht3200.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume II., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jht3201','letter','1779-11-05','Hartford','CT','US','Jonathan','Trumbull','','George','Washington','','individual','','The keeping up large guards of the militia on the coasts, besides the enormous expense attending, injures the public service by withdrawing the men from the field, and lessening our ability to supply the army with men or provisions.','ltr_jht3201.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume II., Jared Sparks, 1853');
